"Why waste resources on educating these inferior beings when they can never amount to anything? It is better to keep them in their place and use them for the benefit of those who are truly worthy."

Dolores was horrified by the words she read. She could not believe that such a reprehensible argument had been made in the past and that it had been accepted as normal. She felt a deep sense of anger and sadness, knowing that this was just one example of the many ways in which Black people had been oppressed and dehumanized throughout history.

As she continued her journey, Dolores made it her mission to spread awareness about these forgotten books and the harmful ideologies they contained. She wanted to make sure that these stories were never forgotten and that future generations could learn from the past.